title.narrative: NUTRITION AND FIRST 1000 DAYS

description.narrative: Government and partners have enhanced capacity to plan, deliver, and monitor coordinated multi-sectoral, gender-responsive, risk- informed approaches at scale for improved access to nutritious diets to reduce stunting and other forms of malnutrition, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Early Childhood Development, Evaluation And Research, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Sanitation, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, more children, adolescents and women, particularly the most vulnerable, benefit from improved and equitable neonatal, child, maternal and adolescent health and nutrition services, and adopt healthy life practices.

description.narrative: Under the leadership of Department of Health and National Nutrition Council, UNICEF and partners supported the development of key nutrition policies, and the Implementing Rules and Regulations of RA 11148 - the Kalusugan at Nutrisyon ng Mag-Nanay Act (the First 1000 Days Act). The Rules and Regulations provide national policy guidance for strengthening nutrition governance, scaling up both preventive and therapeutic nutrition-specific and nutrition-sensitive interventions. At the Provincial and Municipal level, UNICEF also provided strategic technical support in developing multi-sectoral nutrition and WASH plans and strengthening subnational capacities to plan, deliver and monitor quality services even during emergencies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
